features.name: SSB Plays an important role in DNA replication, recombination and repair. Binds to ssDNA and to an array of partner proteins to recruit them to their sites of action during DNA metabolism

APH,Acetyltransf_8 Involved in resistance to gentamicin, tobramycin, and kanamycin. Tobramycin and kanamycin resistance is due to the ACC activity, specified by N-terminal region. The C-terminal region is a kinase that phosphorylates several 4,6-disubstituted aminoglycosides
